ssively on the current costs of growth while undervaluing the future revenue that is already contractually secured. The $50 billion backlog is not a projection; it is a material commitment from two of the most well-capitalized and sophisticated customers in the world. This fundamentally de-risks the execution story. The high beta and current unprofitability have created a compelling entry point for a long-term position.  I will adopt the proposed strategic execution plan as it is well-suited to the high-volatility nature of this asset:  1.  **Scaled Entry:** I will initiate a one-third position at the current market price to establish a stake. 2.  **Disciplined Additions:** I will place limit orders to add the second third on a 10-15% pullback and will reserve the final third for either a further significant decline or a positive catalyst, such as an earnings report confirming execution progress. 3.  **Thesis-Based Risk Management:** My primary risk indicator is the integrity of the Meta and Microsoft contracts. I will monitor all relevant news flow, and any credible report of a cancellation or material alteration to these agreements will trigger an immediate exit from the position. 4.  **Long-Term Horizon:** I am treating this as an 18-36 month investment, allowing the thesis time to play out as the company builds out its infrastructure and begins to recognize revenue from its backlog.  The current market fear provides the opportunity. The contractual backlog provides the conviction.  FINAL TRANSACTION PROPOSAL: **BUY**
